events.description: Roman emperor Claudius dies from poisoning under mysterious circumstances. He is succeeded by his adoptive son Nero, rather than by Britannicus, his son with Messalina.
events.html: • 54 – Roman emperor Claudius dies from poisoning under mysterious circumstances. He is succeeded by his adoptive son Nero, rather than by Britannicus, his son with Messalina.[1]

events.description: Vandals and Alans cross the Pyrenees and appear in Hispania.
events.html: • 409 – Vandals and Alans cross the Pyrenees and appear in Hispania.

events.description: The present church building at Westminster Abbey is consecrated.
events.html: • 1269 – The present church building at Westminster Abbey is consecrated.

events.description: Hundreds of the Knights Templar in France are arrested at dawn by King Philip the Fair, and later confess under torture to heresy.
events.html: • 1307 – Hundreds of the Knights Templar in France are arrested at dawn by King Philip the Fair, and later confess under torture to heresy.

events.description: Rinchinbal Khan becomes the Khagan of the Mongols and Emperor of the Yuan dynasty, reigning for only 53 days.
events.html: • 1332 – Rinchinbal Khan becomes the Khagan of the Mongols and Emperor of the Yuan dynasty, reigning for only 53 days.

events.description: Coronation of Henry IV of England at Westminster Abbey.
events.html: • 1399 – Coronation of Henry IV of England at Westminster Abbey.[2][3]

events.description: A Swedish–Dutch fleet defeats the Danish fleet at Fehmarn and captures about 1,000 prisoners.
events.html: • 1644 – A Swedish–Dutch fleet defeats the Danish fleet at Fehmarn and captures about 1,000 prisoners.

events.description: Port Royal, the capital of French Acadia, falls in a siege by British forces.
events.html: • 1710 – Port Royal, the capital of French Acadia, falls in a siege by British forces.

events.description: The Continental Congress establishes the Continental Navy (predecessor of the United States Navy).
events.html: • 1775 – The Continental Congress establishes the Continental Navy (predecessor of the United States Navy).

events.description: In Washington, D.C., the cornerstone of the United States Executive Mansion (known as the White House since 1818) is laid.
events.html: • 1792 – In Washington, D.C., the cornerstone of the United States Executive Mansion (known as the White House since 1818) is laid.

events.description: French Revolutionary Wars: Austro-Prussian victory over Republican France at the First Battle of Wissembourg.
events.html: • 1793 – French Revolutionary Wars: Austro-Prussian victory over Republican France at the First Battle of Wissembourg.

events.description: War of 1812: Sir Isaac Brock's British and native forces repel an invasion of Canada by General Rensselaer's United States forces.
events.html: • 1812 – War of 1812: Sir Isaac Brock's British and native forces repel an invasion of Canada by General Rensselaer's United States forces.

events.description: The Declaration of Independence of the Mexican Empire is publicly proclaimed.
events.html: • 1821 – The Declaration of Independence of the Mexican Empire is publicly proclaimed.

entities.name: Declaration of Independence of the Mexican Empire

events.description: In New York City, B'nai B'rith, the oldest Jewish service organization in the world, is founded.
events.html: • 1843 – In New York City, B'nai B'rith, the oldest Jewish service organization in the world, is founded.

events.description: First known conversation in modern Hebrew by Eliezer Ben-Yehuda and friends.
events.html: • 1881 – First known conversation in modern Hebrew by Eliezer Ben-Yehuda and friends.

events.description: The Georgia Institute of Technology is founded in Atlanta, Georgia.
events.html: • 1885 – The Georgia Institute of Technology is founded in Atlanta, Georgia.

events.description: Edward Emerson Barnard is first to discover a comet by photographic means.
events.html: • 1892 – Edward Emerson Barnard is first to discover a comet by photographic means.

events.description: The Boston Red Sox win the first modern World Series, defeating the Pittsburgh Pirates in the eighth game.
events.html: • 1903 – The Boston Red Sox win the first modern World Series, defeating the Pittsburgh Pirates in the eighth game.

events.description: Margaret Travers Symons bursts into the UK parliament and becomes the first woman to speak there.
events.html: • 1908 – Margaret Travers Symons bursts into the UK parliament and becomes the first woman to speak there.[4]

events.description: Prince Arthur, Duke of Connaught and Strathearn, becomes the first Governor General of Canada of royal descent.
events.html: • 1911 – Prince Arthur, Duke of Connaught and Strathearn, becomes the first Governor General of Canada of royal descent.

entities.name: Prince Arthur, Duke of Connaught and Strathearn

events.description: First World War: The Battle of the Hohenzollern Redoubt marks the end of the Battle of Loos.
events.html: • 1915 – First World War: The Battle of the Hohenzollern Redoubt marks the end of the Battle of Loos.

events.description: The "Miracle of the Sun" is witnessed by an estimated 70,000 people in the Cova da Iria in Portugal.
events.html: • 1917 – The "Miracle of the Sun" is witnessed by an estimated 70,000 people in the Cova da Iria in Portugal.

events.description: Soviet republics sign the Treaty of Kars to formalize the borders between Turkey and the South Caucasus states.
events.html: • 1921 – Soviet republics sign the Treaty of Kars to formalize the borders between Turkey and the South Caucasus states.

events.description: Ankara becomes the capital of Turkey.
events.html: • 1923 – Ankara becomes the capital of Turkey.

events.description: World War II: Marshal Pietro Badoglio announces that Italy has officially declared war on Germany.
events.html: • 1943 – World War II: Marshal Pietro Badoglio announces that Italy has officially declared war on Germany.

events.description: World War II: The Soviet Riga Offensive captures the city.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Soviet Riga Offensive captures the city.

events.description: France adopts the constitution of the Fourth Republic.
events.html: • 1946 – France adopts the constitution of the Fourth Republic.

events.description: The Pacific Northwest experiences a cyclone the equal of a Category 3 hurricane, with winds above 150 mph. Forty-six people die.
events.html: • 1962 – The Pacific Northwest experiences a cyclone the equal of a Category 3 hurricane, with winds above 150 mph. Forty-six people die.

events.description: Aeroflot Flight 217 crashes outside Moscow, killing 174.
events.html: • 1972 – Aeroflot Flight 217 crashes outside Moscow, killing 174.

events.description: Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571 crashes in the Andes mountains. Twenty-eight survive the crash. All but 16 succumb before rescue on December 23.
events.html: • 1972 – Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571 crashes in the Andes mountains. Twenty-eight survive the crash. All but 16 succumb before rescue on December 23.[5]

events.description: The first electron micrograph of an Ebola virus is taken at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention by Dr. F. A. Murphy.
events.html: • 1976 – The first electron micrograph of an Ebola virus is taken at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention by Dr. F. A. Murphy.

entities.name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention

events.description: A Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano Boeing 707 crashes after takeoff from El Trompillo Airport in Santa Cruz de la Sierra, Bolivia, killing 91.
events.html: • 1976 – A Lloyd Aéreo Boliviano Boeing 707 crashes after takeoff from El Trompillo Airport in Santa Cruz de la Sierra, Bolivia, killing 91.[6]

events.description: Hijacking of Lufthansa Flight 181 by the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine.
events.html: • 1977 – Hijacking of Lufthansa Flight 181 by the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine.

entities.name: Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine

events.description: Ameritech Mobile Communications launches the first US cellular network in Chicago.
events.html: • 1983 – Ameritech Mobile Communications launches the first US cellular network in Chicago.

events.description: Syrian forces attack free areas of Lebanon, removing General Michel Aoun from the presidential palace.
events.html: • 1990 – Syrian forces attack free areas of Lebanon, removing General Michel Aoun from the presidential palace.

events.description: At least 60 people die in eastern Papua New Guinea when a series of earthquakes rock the Finisterre Range, triggering massive landslides.
events.html: • 1993 – At least 60 people die in eastern Papua New Guinea when a series of earthquakes rock the Finisterre Range, triggering massive landslides.[7]

events.description: The mining accident in Copiapó, Chile ends as all 33 trapped miners arrive at the surface after a record 69 days underground.
events.html: • 2010 – The mining accident in Copiapó, Chile ends as all 33 trapped miners arrive at the surface after a record 69 days underground.

events.description: A stampede occurs in India during the Hindu festival Navratri, killing 115 and injuring more than 110.
events.html: • 2013 – A stampede occurs in India during the Hindu festival Navratri, killing 115 and injuring more than 110.

events.description: The Maldives announces its decision to withdraw from the Commonwealth of Nations.
events.html: • 2016 – The Maldives announces its decision to withdraw from the Commonwealth of Nations.

events.html: • 2019 – Kenyan Brigid Kosgei sets a new world record for a woman runner with a time of 2:14:04 at the 2019 Chicago Marathon.[8]
